1
00:00:03,703 --> 00:00:05,370
-ONCE UPON A TIME,

2
00:00:05,370 --> 00:00:08,703
THERE WAS A MAN
WHO FELL IN LOVE WITH A DOLL.

3
00:00:08,703 --> 00:00:11,703
PERHAPS THE MAN'S LOVE
MADE ITSELF FELT.

4
00:00:11,703 --> 00:00:15,703
FOR ONE DAY, THE DOLL CAME
TO LIFE AND BEGAN TO DANCE.

5
00:00:15,703 --> 00:00:18,536
THE MAN WAS DELIGHTED.

6
00:00:18,536 --> 00:00:21,703
HE THOUGHT A DOLL
WOULD NEVER BETRAY HIS LOVE

7
00:00:21,703 --> 00:00:23,370
AND THAT NOW HE COULD
HAVE THE WORLD'S

8
00:00:23,370 --> 00:00:27,870
MOST PURE AND INNOCENT LOVE
ALL TO HIMSELF.

9
00:00:27,870 --> 00:00:30,370
UNFORTUNATELY FOR HIM,

10
00:00:30,370 --> 00:00:34,703
THE DOLL WHO HAD BEEN GIVEN LIFE
REJECTED THE MAN'S LOVE

11
00:00:34,703 --> 00:00:37,236
AND FELL IN LOVE
WITH ANOTHER MAN.

12
00:00:40,670 --> 00:00:43,203
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

13
00:00:55,236 --> 00:00:58,270
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

14
00:01:23,070 --> 00:01:27,170
[ SINGING CONTINUES ]

15
00:02:10,103 --> 00:02:12,836
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S "FINAL
WALTZ AND APOTHEOSIS" FROM
"THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

16
00:02:31,310 --> 00:02:33,310
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

17
00:02:35,433 --> 00:02:38,900
-OH, I COULDN'T SLEEP.

18
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:40,400
MYTHO...

19
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,833
I WONDER WHY HE DID THAT.

20
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
FOR HIM TO JUMP OUT
OF THE WINDOW LIKE THAT,

21
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,533
COULD IT BE 'CAUSE HIS HEART

22
00:02:50,533 --> 00:02:53,133
HASN'T BEEN
COMPLETELY RETURNED YET?

23
00:02:53,133 --> 00:02:55,000
THEN I'VE GOT TO TRY
EVEN HARDER

24
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,733
TO GET THE REST OF HIS HEART
BACK FOR HIM AND DO IT QUICKLY!

25
00:03:01,433 --> 00:03:03,900
-WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?

26
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:14,900
-MYTHO WAS CALLED
INTO THE OFFICE!

27
00:03:14,900 --> 00:03:16,500
-THIS IS SERIOUS!
-HUH?

28
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,233
-NO WAY!
-SENIOR FAKIR?

29
00:03:18,233 --> 00:03:19,333
-HE WAS CALLED TO!

30
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:20,900
-OH, MUST BE
FOR THE PUSHING INCIDENT.

31
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:23,367
-HUH, PUSHING IN--
-YOU DON'T KNOW, DUCK?

32
00:03:23,367 --> 00:03:26,767
THE WONDERFUL FAKIR PUSHED THE
WONDERFUL AND UNRESISTING MYTHO

33
00:03:26,767 --> 00:03:28,733
OUT OF THE WINDOW!
-WHAT?!

34
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:30,600
THERE'S GOT TO BE SOME KIND
OF MISTAKE

35
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:32,133
'CAUSE MYTHO JUMPED OUT HIMSELF!

36
00:03:32,133 --> 00:03:34,700
IT WASN'T --
-AS IF HE'D DO THAT.

37
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:37,667
-EVERYONE WAS WATCHING,
SO EXCUSES WON'T WORK.

38
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:38,833
-BUT IT...

39
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,533
-THAT WAS JUST TOO CRUEL,
EVEN FOR FAKIR.

40
00:03:49,533 --> 00:03:53,067
-OH, I HOPE HE BECOMES
A FULL-FLEDGED CRIMINAL

41
00:03:53,067 --> 00:03:54,933
AND PLUNGES HEADLONG
DOWN THE PATH

42
00:03:54,933 --> 00:03:56,900
TO BECOMING ONE OF LIFE'S
LOSERS!

43
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:58,933
-ANYWAY, LET'S GO SEE!
-YES, LET'S!

44
00:03:58,933 --> 00:04:02,933
-[ Thinking ] BUT WHEN
I SAW HIM, I'M SURE THAT HE...

45
00:04:02,933 --> 00:04:07,100
[ GRUNTING ]

46
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:08,900
-SHH!
-OH.

47
00:04:08,900 --> 00:04:11,033
FINE, THEN!

48
00:04:11,033 --> 00:04:12,600
[ WHISTLE! ]

49
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:15,133
QUACK!
[ SPARKLE! ]

50
00:04:15,133 --> 00:04:17,367
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK, QUACK,
QUACK, QUACK, QUACK, QUACK!

51
00:04:17,367 --> 00:04:22,133
-UNPLEASANT INCIDENTS JUST KEEP
HAPPENING LATELY, DON'T THEY?

52
00:04:22,133 --> 00:04:25,467
WHAT EXACTLY HAPPENED YESTERDAY?

53
00:04:25,467 --> 00:04:29,933
-[ GRUNTING ]

54
00:04:29,933 --> 00:04:32,800
THAT WAS SIMPLY DUE
TO MY CARELESSNESS.

55
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,533
-WHAT?

56
00:04:34,533 --> 00:04:37,333
-JUST AN ACCIDENT.
-[ GASPS ]

57
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:39,300
-ACCIDENT?
-YES.

58
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:41,200
I'M SORRY TO HAVE CAUSED
YOU WORRY.

59
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,233
-WHY WOULD YOU LIE LIKE THAT?

60
00:04:43,233 --> 00:04:46,133
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN, MR. FAKIR?

61
00:04:46,133 --> 00:04:48,000
I MUST SAY,

62
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,933
I AM RELUCTANT TO ACCEPT
THE ACCIDENT EXPLANATION MYSELF.

63
00:04:51,933 --> 00:04:53,333
-ARE YOU SAYING YOU BELIEVE

64
00:04:53,333 --> 00:04:56,233
THAT FAKIR PUSHED ME
OUT OF THE WINDOW, MR. CAT?

65
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:59,300
-ARGUMENTS CAN SOMETIMES
HAPPEN, MR. MYTHO.

66
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:01,967
FOR EXAMPLE,
ALBRECHT AND HILARION

67
00:05:01,967 --> 00:05:04,367
BOTH WANTED TO MARRY
THE MAIDEN GISELLE!

68
00:05:04,367 --> 00:05:06,267
[ GROWLS ]

69
00:05:06,267 --> 00:05:09,033
THEIR DESIRE
TO MARRY HER CAUSED THEM TO...

70
00:05:09,033 --> 00:05:12,033
[ SCREAMS ]

71
00:05:12,033 --> 00:05:14,033
[ GROANS ]

72
00:05:14,033 --> 00:05:17,300
I SUPPOSE YOU'RE A LITTLE YOUNG
FOR THAT PARTICULAR PROBLEM.

73
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:19,200
WELL, THAT'S FINE,

74
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:21,833
BUT I CANNOT LET YOU CONTINUE
TO LIVE IN ONE ROOM!

75
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:24,533
-THEN I WILL --
-I WILL LEAVE.

76
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:25,900
-FAKIR...

77
00:05:27,267 --> 00:05:29,767
[ ALL SCREAM ]

78
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:35,867
-QUITE AUDACIOUS OF YOU
TO BE EAVESDROPPING ON ME!

79
00:05:35,867 --> 00:05:37,733
KEEP IT UP,
AND I'LL HAVE YOU MARRY --

80
00:05:37,733 --> 00:05:39,200
[ ALL SCREAM ]

81
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,733
[ SIGHS ]
-QUACK.

82
00:05:40,733 --> 00:05:44,833
-[ SLURPING, PURRING ]

83
00:05:44,833 --> 00:05:47,733
-[ GASPS ]
-[ CHUCKLES ]

84
00:05:47,733 --> 00:05:50,200
-[ GASPS ] THOSE EYES AGAIN.

85
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,833
WHAT'S HAPPENED TO YOU, MYTHO?

86
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:53,833
-HE LOOKS LIKE HE'S IN PAIN.

87
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:55,200
-WELL, HE WAS BETRAYED
BY THE PERSON

88
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,867
HE THOUGHT WAS HIS BEST FRIEND.

89
00:05:56,867 --> 00:05:59,133
-I BET HE COVERED
FOR SENIOR FAKIR ANYWAY.

90
00:05:59,133 --> 00:06:00,833
-THAT'S SO LIKE HIM.

91
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:06,267
-[ GROANS ]

92
00:06:06,267 --> 00:06:08,267
-QUACK! OH.

93
00:06:08,267 --> 00:06:11,667
-WHO ARE YOU?

94
00:06:11,667 --> 00:06:13,267
-HUH?

95
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:15,467
-WHY --
WHY ARE YOU INSIDE OF ME?

96
00:06:15,467 --> 00:06:18,000
-[ Thinking ]
WHO IS HE TALKING TO?

97
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,433
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]
-UH...

98
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,533
-PIKE?

99
00:06:24,533 --> 00:06:28,067
-UM, YOU KNOW, THIS MIGHT BE
NONE OF MY BUSINESS,

100
00:06:28,067 --> 00:06:32,033
BUT I THINK
YOU'RE MAKING A BIG MISTAKE.

101
00:06:32,033 --> 00:06:34,600
I'M TALKING ABOUT SENIOR FAKIR.

102
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,867
YOU TWO HAVE BEEN FRIENDS
FOR A LONG TIME,

103
00:06:36,867 --> 00:06:38,467
SO IT'S NOT
THAT I DON'T UNDERSTAND

104
00:06:38,467 --> 00:06:41,533
WHY YOU'D WANT TO COVER FOR HIM
IN FRONT OF MR. CAT,

105
00:06:41,533 --> 00:06:44,633
BUT IF SOMETHING
LIKE THIS HAPPENS A SECOND TIME,

106
00:06:44,633 --> 00:06:47,767
YOU MIGHT END UP NEVER BEING
ABLE TO DANCE AGAIN OR WORSE.

107
00:06:47,767 --> 00:06:50,767
-WHY ARE YOU TALKING TO ME
ABOUT THIS?

108
00:06:50,767 --> 00:06:52,533
-UH, YESTERDAY, I SAW YOU.

109
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:55,000
I SAW YOU GLIDING DOWN
FROM THE SKY

110
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:57,100
WITH THIS ENORMOUS WHITE BIRD
NEXT TO YOU.

111
00:06:57,100 --> 00:07:00,567
-UH...
-WHEN I SAW THAT...

112
00:07:00,567 --> 00:07:02,967
I THOUGHT MAYBE YOU
WERE BEING PROTECTED

113
00:07:02,967 --> 00:07:06,000
BY, LIKE, THE GOD OF DANCE
OR SOMETHING.

114
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,867
-[ Thinking ] WHITE BIRD.
DOES SHE MEAN TUTU?

115
00:07:08,867 --> 00:07:11,533
-YOU SAY SUCH CUTE THINGS, PIKE,

116
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:14,000
AND YOU HAVE A FORTHRIGHT,
STEADFAST,

117
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,300
AND BEAUTIFUL HEART BEATING
WITHIN YOU.

118
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:17,700
-[ GASPS ]

119
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:21,000
UH...

120
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,067
UH, EXCUSE ME! I HAVE TO GO!

121
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:26,100
-PIKE...

122
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:31,100
-[ GIGGLES ]
I SAW THAT, I SAW THAT!

123
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:33,833
-OH.

124
00:07:37,167 --> 00:07:38,500
QUACK.

125
00:07:39,733 --> 00:07:41,933
[ GASPS ]

126
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:46,067
HE'S GONE.

127
00:07:46,067 --> 00:07:49,333
A CROW'S FEATHER?

128
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:52,067
IS THIS...

129
00:07:52,067 --> 00:07:54,333
I KNOW. I'LL GO TALK TO FAKIR!

130
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:57,233
ANYWAY, I HAVE TO TURN BACK
INTO A GIRL SOMEWHERE.

131
00:07:57,233 --> 00:07:59,933
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]
[ BEEP! BEEP! BEEP! ]

132
00:07:59,933 --> 00:08:02,500
NO GOOD -- TOO MANY PEOPLE.

133
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,633
I GOT IT.

134
00:08:07,567 --> 00:08:09,433
THIS PLACE SHOULD BE OKAY.

135
00:08:09,433 --> 00:08:10,933
[ SPLASH! ]

136
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:12,533
[ SPARKLE! ]

137
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:14,900
-[ GRUNTING ]

138
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:20,267
MAN, I REALLY
DANCED MY BUTT OFF.

139
00:08:20,267 --> 00:08:23,133
[ SIGHS ]

140
00:08:25,467 --> 00:08:28,233
HUH, HUH?

141
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:30,067
[ SIGHS ]

142
00:08:30,067 --> 00:08:32,700
HUH?

143
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:35,167
OH, WHERE DID DYLAN GO?

144
00:08:35,167 --> 00:08:36,700
-UH-OH.

145
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:38,800
-MR. ARMADYLAN!

146
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:41,567
-YES, SIR.

147
00:08:41,567 --> 00:08:45,100
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
-OH!

148
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,767
HE SCARED ME!

149
00:08:46,767 --> 00:08:49,167
WAIT, THERE'S NO TIME
FOR WORRYING!

150
00:08:49,167 --> 00:08:51,433
I WONDER WHERE FAKIR IS.

151
00:08:51,433 --> 00:08:52,567
OH!

152
00:08:52,567 --> 00:08:54,233
-HEY, IS SOMETHING
GOING ON WITH HIM?

153
00:08:54,233 --> 00:08:55,900
-WITH FAKIR.
-HE'S ACTING WEIRD.

154
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:57,500
-HE'S UP IN THE LIBRARY.

155
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,467
-HOLED UP IN THERE.

156
00:08:58,467 --> 00:09:00,900
-LIBRARY?

157
00:09:04,067 --> 00:09:06,100
HMM.

158
00:09:09,067 --> 00:09:10,733
HE'S REALLY HERE!

159
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:14,167
HEY, FAKIR, JUST NOW,
MYTHO AND PIKE --

160
00:09:14,167 --> 00:09:16,000
AND IT WAS REALLY WEIRD,
AND MYTHO WAS --

161
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,200
AND WHAT HAPPENED YESTERDAY
WAS WEIRD, TOO,

162
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,533
AND I THOUGHT MEOWSINSKI'S
SHOES MIGHT BE MYTHO'S FAULT,

163
00:09:20,533 --> 00:09:22,467
BUT THAT COULD JUST
BE MY IMAGINATION.

164
00:09:22,467 --> 00:09:25,367
BUT -- BUT -- BUT IT REALLY
WAS SUPER WEIRD, SO MYTHO WAS --

165
00:09:25,367 --> 00:09:27,633
-CAN YOU PLEASE BE
A LITTLE QUIETER?

166
00:09:27,633 --> 00:09:29,933
-MYTHO! OH, I'M SORRY.

167
00:09:29,933 --> 00:09:32,133
-CALM DOWN.
-MM.

168
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:34,633
DID SOMETHING HAPPEN TO MYTHO?

169
00:09:34,633 --> 00:09:36,633
-THAT'S WHAT I'M TRYING
TO FIND OUT.

170
00:09:36,633 --> 00:09:38,033
-AND WHAT HAPPENED YESTERDAY?

171
00:09:38,033 --> 00:09:40,467
MYTHO JUMPED OUT THE WINDOW
HIMSELF, DIDN'T HE?

172
00:09:40,467 --> 00:09:41,867
BUT IN FRONT OF MR. CAT,

173
00:09:41,867 --> 00:09:44,767
HE MADE IT SOUND LIKE
HE WAS JUST COVERING FOR YOU,

174
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:47,467
AND THAT MADE IT LOOK LIKE
YOU WERE THE BAD GUY.

175
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:49,300
[ BOOK CLOSES ]

176
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:51,933
OH, AND JUST NOW,
I WAS FOLLOWING MYTHO AROUND

177
00:09:51,933 --> 00:09:53,000
TO SEE WHAT WAS UP,

178
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,833
AND THEN HE VANISHED
ALL OF A SUDDEN.

179
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,333
HE LEFT BEHIND...

180
00:09:58,233 --> 00:09:59,867
...A CROW'S FEATHER.

181
00:09:59,867 --> 00:10:01,067
-WHAT?!

182
00:10:05,967 --> 00:10:07,933
-HUH?
-OH!

183
00:10:07,933 --> 00:10:10,167
WHY DID YOU STOP?

184
00:10:10,167 --> 00:10:12,167
OH.
-[ CHUCKLES ]

185
00:10:12,167 --> 00:10:15,800
-IT'S RUE! FAKIR?

186
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:18,333
FAKIR!
-YOU DID THIS!

187
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:19,367
WHAT DID YOU DO TO MYTHO?

188
00:10:19,367 --> 00:10:20,700
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

189
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:22,633
-DON'T PLAY DUMB WITH ME!

190
00:10:22,633 --> 00:10:25,067
-LET GO OF ME! THAT HURTS!
-SHOW YOUR TRUE COLORS!

191
00:10:25,067 --> 00:10:28,467
KRAEHE.
-[ CHUCKLES ]

192
00:10:30,767 --> 00:10:31,833
-STOP IT.

193
00:10:34,767 --> 00:10:36,133
-LET GO OF ME!

194
00:10:36,133 --> 00:10:38,700
[ SLAP! ]

195
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:40,267
[ ALL GASP ]

196
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,900
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

197
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:54,433
I'LL BE JUST FINE.

198
00:10:54,433 --> 00:10:55,867
-SO LIKE MYTHO.

199
00:10:55,867 --> 00:10:57,533
-HE'S INCREDIBLY MATURE.

200
00:10:57,533 --> 00:11:01,200
-AS MUCH AS FAKIR'S IMMATURE.

201
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,633
-OH, DEAR.

202
00:11:02,633 --> 00:11:05,267
DUCK'S PRINCE IS CHANGING

203
00:11:05,267 --> 00:11:07,567
AND NOT FOR THE BETTER,
I'M AFRAID.

204
00:11:07,567 --> 00:11:10,233
DO SOMETHING FAST, LITTLE DUCK,

205
00:11:10,233 --> 00:11:14,333
BEFORE THE BEAUTIFUL SPARKLE
IN THE EYES UNDER THAT EVIL MASK

206
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:17,233
FADES COMPLETELY.

207
00:11:18,433 --> 00:11:21,667
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"NUTCRACKER: MARCH" PLAYS ]

208
00:11:27,016 --> 00:11:30,983
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"NUTCRACKER: MARCH" PLAYS ]

209
00:11:33,316 --> 00:11:35,607
-[ GROANS ]

210
00:11:35,607 --> 00:11:37,440
-ARE YOU IN PAIN, FATHER?

211
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:39,040
-[ GROANS ]

212
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:42,474
I WANT TO LEAVE THIS PLACE
AS SOON AS I CAN.

213
00:11:42,474 --> 00:11:43,807
IF I WERE FREE,

214
00:11:43,807 --> 00:11:46,574
I COULD WRAP THESE WINGS
AROUND MY DEAR DAUGHTER

215
00:11:46,574 --> 00:11:48,640
AND HUG HER AS MUCH AS I WANTED.

216
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:52,040
-YOU ONLY NEED ENDURE
IT A LITTLE LONGER, FATHER.

217
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:54,674
IT LOOKS LIKE THE PRINCE
HAS FOUND US OUR PREY.

218
00:11:54,674 --> 00:11:55,907
-THE PRINCE HAS?

219
00:11:55,907 --> 00:11:57,707
OH.

220
00:11:57,707 --> 00:12:00,407
-I'M SO GLAD I OBEYED
YOUR INSTRUCTIONS, FATHER.

221
00:12:06,207 --> 00:12:08,840
YES.

222
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:12,607
IF I HAD NOT SOAKED THE HEART
SHARD WITH THE FEELING OF LOVE

223
00:12:12,607 --> 00:12:16,107
AND FATHER'S BLOOD
THAT DAY LIKE HE TOLD ME TO,

224
00:12:16,107 --> 00:12:19,574
MY PRINCE WOULD NOT HAVE
RETURNED TO ME.

225
00:12:28,107 --> 00:12:30,174
I HAVE TO BE GRATEFUL
TO PRINCESS TUTU

226
00:12:30,174 --> 00:12:32,607
FOR GIVING THE HEART SHARD BACK
TO HIM.

227
00:12:32,607 --> 00:12:34,874
-IT WOULD SERVE YOU WELL, ALSO,

228
00:12:34,874 --> 00:12:37,840
TO BE ACCOMMODATING
TO PRINCESS TUTU.

229
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,707
IN ORDER TO BREAK THE SEAL
TO RELEASE ME,

230
00:12:40,707 --> 00:12:44,040
WE HAVE TO FIND THE REST
OF THE PRINCE'S HEART SHARDS.

231
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:47,340
WE NEED PRINCESS TUTU'S POWER
TO DO THAT.

232
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:50,274
IF YOU TRY TO GET
RID OF HER AGAIN,

233
00:12:50,274 --> 00:12:53,174
I'LL SHOW YOU NO MERCY,
DAUGHTER OR NOT!

234
00:12:53,174 --> 00:12:55,207
-I'M SORRY! I WON'T, FATHER!

235
00:12:55,207 --> 00:12:57,240
-GOOD!

236
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:59,340
-HEY, THERE, RUE.

237
00:12:59,340 --> 00:13:03,374
-OTHER THAN MYSELF, NO ONE
BUT THE PRINCE IN THE STORY

238
00:13:03,374 --> 00:13:06,374
CAN TRULY LOVE
A PITIFUL PERSON LIKE YOU,

239
00:13:06,374 --> 00:13:08,674
WHO, DESPITE BEING A CROW,

240
00:13:08,674 --> 00:13:12,374
HAD BEEN BORN
INTO THIS HIDEOUS HUMAN BODY.

241
00:13:12,374 --> 00:13:14,107
I AM SURE WE WOULD BOTH LIKE

242
00:13:14,107 --> 00:13:17,707
TO SEE YOUR WEDDING DAY
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

243
00:13:17,707 --> 00:13:20,640
-THANK YOU, FATHER.

244
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:27,907
-I FEEL LIKE THAT DAY
WAS SUCH A LONG TIME AGO.

245
00:13:27,907 --> 00:13:30,340
-DUCK!

246
00:13:30,340 --> 00:13:33,340
HAPPY NEWS!

247
00:13:33,340 --> 00:13:34,607
-OH, WHAT?

248
00:13:34,607 --> 00:13:36,540
-WELL, I JUST HEARD
STARTING TOMORROW,

249
00:13:36,540 --> 00:13:40,040
THE WONDERFUL FAKIR IS SUSPENDED
FROM SCHOOL FOR A WHOLE WEEK!

250
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:42,207
-NO WAY!
-YES WAY!

251
00:13:42,207 --> 00:13:45,774
AT THIS RATE, HE'LL GRADUATE
FROM JUVIE TO FELON IN NO TIME!

252
00:13:45,774 --> 00:13:47,407
-FAKIR WAS...

253
00:13:47,407 --> 00:13:48,907
-MORE IMPORTANTLY...
-OH.

254
00:13:48,907 --> 00:13:51,474
-...JUST NOW WHILE I JUST
HAPPENED TO BE FOLLOWING PIKE,

255
00:13:51,474 --> 00:13:53,740
I JUST HAPPENED TO SEE
HER MEET UP WITH MYTHO,

256
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:55,574
AND AS I JUST HAPPENED TO
KEEP FOLLOWING THEM,

257
00:13:55,574 --> 00:13:56,774
THEY WENT OFF TO A PLACE

258
00:13:56,774 --> 00:13:58,807
WHERE THERE WAS ABSOLUTELY
NO ONE AROUND.

259
00:13:58,807 --> 00:13:59,974
[ GIGGLES ]

260
00:13:59,974 --> 00:14:01,974
-PIKE WAS WITH MYTHO?

261
00:14:01,974 --> 00:14:04,474
-WELL, WANT TO
IT JUST HAPPENED TO GO SEE?

262
00:14:04,474 --> 00:14:06,607
-MM.
-THAT'S THE SPIRIT!

263
00:14:06,607 --> 00:14:10,240
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

264
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:12,374
SEE?
-[ GASPS ]

265
00:14:13,907 --> 00:14:15,107
-PIKE...

266
00:14:15,107 --> 00:14:17,407
[ BOING! BOING! BOING! BOING!
WHISTLE! ]

267
00:14:17,407 --> 00:14:19,174
-HEY, HOLD ON!

268
00:14:19,174 --> 00:14:21,407
-DUCK, WHAT'S --
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

269
00:14:21,407 --> 00:14:23,707
-UM, UH, YOU SEE --
-WHAT'S WRONG?

270
00:14:23,707 --> 00:14:25,407
YOU HAVE A PROBLEM WITH THIS?

271
00:14:25,407 --> 00:14:27,974
JUST WHAT DO YOU CARE
IF MYTHO AND I ARE DATING?

272
00:14:27,974 --> 00:14:29,107
THAT'S OUR BUSINESS!

273
00:14:29,107 --> 00:14:31,940
-WHAT?
MYTHO, YOU LIKE PIKE?

274
00:14:32,974 --> 00:14:36,507
[ Thinking ] THOSE EYES AGAIN.

275
00:14:36,507 --> 00:14:38,740
MYTHO, WHAT'S HAPPENED TO YOU?

276
00:14:38,740 --> 00:14:40,140
SOMETHING'S WEIRD HERE.

277
00:14:40,140 --> 00:14:41,940
-WHAT'S SO WEIRD
ABOUT GOING OUT WITH ME?!

278
00:14:41,940 --> 00:14:43,807
-NO, THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT!

279
00:14:43,807 --> 00:14:45,640
I MEANT YESTERDAY AND STUFF.

280
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:47,440
MYTHO JUMPED OUT THE WINDOW
HIMSELF, BUT --

281
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:49,140
-HUH?
-YOU'RE STILL SAYING THAT?!

282
00:14:49,140 --> 00:14:50,407
-AND MR. CAT'S SHOES.

283
00:14:50,407 --> 00:14:52,807
MYTHO MIGHT'VE --
-WILL YOU CUT IT OUT ALREADY?!

284
00:14:52,807 --> 00:14:54,040
-HUH?
-MYTHO.

285
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:56,374
-JUST WHO...ARE YOU?

286
00:14:56,374 --> 00:14:59,474
WHAT ARE YOU TRYING
TO MAKE ME DO?

287
00:14:59,474 --> 00:15:02,007
-UH...MYTHO, WAIT!

288
00:15:02,007 --> 00:15:04,040
-STAY AWAY!

289
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:05,440
-MYTHO, WHY?

290
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:07,974
-AW, IT WAS JUST
GETTING GOOD, TOO.

291
00:15:07,974 --> 00:15:09,107
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

292
00:15:09,107 --> 00:15:11,407
-HEY, PIKE, PLEASE COME OUT!

293
00:15:11,407 --> 00:15:13,640
-YEAH, LET'S TAKE
THIS OUTSIDE RIGHT NOW!

294
00:15:13,640 --> 00:15:15,540
-WE CAN TALK PEACEFULLY, OKAY?

295
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:16,840
-WE ARE GONNA STRAIGHTEN
A FEW THINGS OUT!

296
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:19,307
-SORRY, BUT BE QUIET
FOR A SECOND.

297
00:15:19,307 --> 00:15:22,907
-HUH? BUT YOU HAVE TO TAKE A
HARSHER TONE WITH YOUR ENEMIES.

298
00:15:22,907 --> 00:15:26,240
-LILIE, I DON'T THINK OF PIKE
AS AN ENEMY.

299
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,907
-UH, REALLY?

300
00:15:27,907 --> 00:15:30,240
DUCK, IS THIS REALLY OKAY?

301
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:32,974
-UH-HUH. THAT'S HOW I FEEL.

302
00:15:32,974 --> 00:15:36,107
-HEY, SHE SAYS AS AN ENEMY,
YOU'RE NOT WORTH THINKING ABOUT!

303
00:15:36,107 --> 00:15:37,774
-NO, THAT ISN'T WHAT I MEANT!

304
00:15:37,774 --> 00:15:39,407
[ LAUGHS ]

305
00:15:39,407 --> 00:15:41,407
-THAT'S ENOUGH FOR TODAY!
LET'S GO!

306
00:15:41,407 --> 00:15:43,240
-WE'LL LET YOU OFF
WITH THIS FOR TODAY!

307
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,607
[ LAUGHS MANICALLY ]

308
00:15:45,607 --> 00:15:48,607
-UH...

309
00:15:48,607 --> 00:15:50,574
MYTHO?

310
00:15:55,007 --> 00:15:57,240
[ DOOR OPENS ]
- [ CHUCKLES ]

311
00:15:57,240 --> 00:16:00,607
-KRAEHE?
-YOU'RE WORKING INTENTLY.

312
00:16:00,607 --> 00:16:04,740
IS THE SUBJECT OF YOUR RESEARCH
PRINCES, OR IS IT RAVENS?

313
00:16:06,207 --> 00:16:10,040
SHALL I TELL YOU WHAT THE PRINCE
IS MOVING TOWARDS BECOMING?

314
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:12,074
-SO YOU DID DO SOMETHING.

315
00:16:12,074 --> 00:16:16,274
-THE HEART SHARD OF LOVE THAT
PRINCESS TUTU GAVE BACK TO HIM,

316
00:16:16,274 --> 00:16:20,174
THAT SHARD WAS SOAKED IN A BATH
OF THE RAVEN'S BLOOD, SO...

317
00:16:20,174 --> 00:16:22,574
-THE RAVEN'S BLOOD? THEN YOU --

318
00:16:22,574 --> 00:16:25,507
-MY FATHER WAS WILLING TO PART
WITH SOME OF HIS OWN BLOOD

319
00:16:25,507 --> 00:16:27,040
FOR THE SAKE OF HIS DAUGHTER.

320
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:29,040
-THE RAVEN'S DAUGHTER?

321
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:30,807
-THE PRINCE WILL SOON CHANGE.

322
00:16:30,807 --> 00:16:32,607
HE'LL LOVE ONLY ME,

323
00:16:32,607 --> 00:16:35,440
AND HE'LL FIND A YOUNG AND
BEAUTIFUL HEART FOR MY FATHER

324
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:38,274
AND OFFER IT UP TO HIM
AS A SACRIFICE.

325
00:16:38,274 --> 00:16:41,240
WHEN THE BLOOD HAS FINISHED
PERMEATING HIS WHOLE HEART,

326
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:43,540
HE WILL NEVER GO BACK
TO THE WAY HE WAS.

327
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:45,907
-DID YOU TELL TUTU
ABOUT ALL THIS?

328
00:16:45,907 --> 00:16:47,440
-I SHOULD.

329
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:50,407
IF I DID THAT, I COULD MAKE
HER SUFFER, COULDN'T I?

330
00:16:50,407 --> 00:16:53,107
OR PERHAPS IT
WOULD BE MORE EFFECTIVE

331
00:16:53,107 --> 00:16:55,040
TO TELL THE PRINCE
THAT SHE IS, IN TRUTH,

332
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:57,907
A GIRL WHO IS REALLY
A WRETCHED EXCUSE FOR A DANCER.

333
00:16:57,907 --> 00:16:59,474
[ CHUCKLES ]

334
00:16:59,474 --> 00:17:02,040
IT WAS STUPID OF YOU
TO BREAK THE PRINCE'S SWORD.

335
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:03,507
WITHOUT THAT BLADE,

336
00:17:03,507 --> 00:17:06,674
YOU CAN'T EVEN HOPE TO TAKE
HIS HEART OUT NOW, CAN YOU?

337
00:17:06,674 --> 00:17:09,440
BUT YOU'RE ONLY HUMAN,
AFTER ALL.

338
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:12,640
MAYBE ALL YOU CAN DO
IS LOOK THINGS UP IN BOOKS.

339
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:14,540
[ LAUGHS ]

340
00:17:22,532 --> 00:17:23,632
-[ GASPS ]

341
00:17:23,632 --> 00:17:25,365
PIKE.

342
00:17:45,765 --> 00:17:47,899
-SORRY ABOUT BEFORE.

343
00:17:47,899 --> 00:17:51,665
I TRULY AND HONESTLY
NEED YOUR LOVE.

344
00:17:51,665 --> 00:17:53,165
-ALL RIGHT, MM.

345
00:17:53,165 --> 00:17:55,299
-ARE YOU AFRAID?

346
00:17:55,299 --> 00:17:57,199
-NO, O-OF COURSE NOT.

347
00:17:57,199 --> 00:17:59,932
-PIKE, PROMISE TO LOVE ONLY ME.

348
00:17:59,932 --> 00:18:01,165
-ALL RIGHT.

349
00:18:01,165 --> 00:18:04,465
-PROMISE ME THAT YOU'LL HATE
EVERYONE ELSE.

350
00:18:04,465 --> 00:18:07,165
-I WILL.
I PROMISE TO LOVE ONLY YOU

351
00:18:07,165 --> 00:18:10,165
AND TO HATE EVERYONE ELSE, TOO.

352
00:18:10,165 --> 00:18:11,399
-PIKE.

353
00:18:11,399 --> 00:18:13,832
-ALL RIGHT, AS PROOF THEN...

354
00:18:13,832 --> 00:18:17,865
YOU'LL GIVE ME
YOUR BEAUTIFUL HEART.

355
00:18:17,865 --> 00:18:19,532
WON'T YOU?

356
00:18:19,532 --> 00:18:21,365
-YES.

357
00:18:21,365 --> 00:18:25,432
-THEN STEP FORWARD.

358
00:18:25,432 --> 00:18:27,632
INTO MY ARMS!

359
00:18:27,632 --> 00:18:29,365
GIVE ME YOUR HEART!
-GIVE ME YOUR HEART!

360
00:18:29,365 --> 00:18:32,732
-[ GASPS ]

361
00:18:32,732 --> 00:18:35,332
[ CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

362
00:18:42,765 --> 00:18:46,565
-THAT'S THE WALTZ OF THE DOLL.
IT'S FROM "COPPéLIA."

363
00:18:46,565 --> 00:18:48,999
-IF I CAN JUST HAVE MYTHO,

364
00:18:48,999 --> 00:18:52,065
I DON'T MIND LOSING MY HEART
AND TURNING INTO A DOLL.

365
00:18:52,065 --> 00:18:53,832
-THE MORE BEAUTIFUL THE HEART,

366
00:18:53,832 --> 00:18:56,932
THE STRONGER THE FRAGRANCE
WHEN IT'S DYED IN EVIL!

367
00:18:56,932 --> 00:18:59,999
- DIDN'T MYTHO FALL IN LOVE
WITH PIKE?

368
00:19:01,632 --> 00:19:04,565
NO, HE MUSTN'T TAKE
PIKE'S HEART!

369
00:19:04,565 --> 00:19:07,132
[ SPARKLE! BUBBLE! BUBBLE! ]

370
00:19:07,132 --> 00:19:09,865
[ SPARKLE! SPARKLE! SPARKLE!
SPARKLE! SPARKLE! ]

371
00:19:14,132 --> 00:19:16,732
[ SPARKLE! SPARKLE! ]

372
00:19:16,732 --> 00:19:19,065
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

373
00:19:21,799 --> 00:19:24,665
WAIT, PLEASE COME DANCE WITH ME.

374
00:19:24,665 --> 00:19:26,165
WON'T YOU, PIKE?

375
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:28,265
-NO.
-TUTU.

376
00:19:28,265 --> 00:19:30,665
[ GRUNTS ]

377
00:19:34,699 --> 00:19:37,399
-OH! PIKE! AGH!

378
00:19:37,399 --> 00:19:39,499
-YOUR PLEAS ARE USELESS.

379
00:19:39,499 --> 00:19:41,632
PIKE HERSELF WANTS
TO GIVE HER HEART TO ME

380
00:19:41,632 --> 00:19:43,665
AND BECOME A SACRIFICE.

381
00:19:43,665 --> 00:19:45,865
AS LONG AS HER FEELINGS
STAY THIS WAY --

382
00:19:45,865 --> 00:19:48,865
-PIKE, STOP!

383
00:19:48,865 --> 00:19:51,365
-IS THIS TRULY WHAT YOU DESIRE?

384
00:19:51,365 --> 00:19:53,799
SWANHILDE FROM "COPPéLIA"
WAS A NORMAL GIRL

385
00:19:53,799 --> 00:19:57,032
MERELY PRETENDING TO BE A DOLL.

386
00:19:57,032 --> 00:19:59,032
JUST LIKE YOU, PIKE --

387
00:19:59,032 --> 00:20:02,599
A GIRL WHO LIKES CHATTING,
SINGING, AND LOVES DANCING.

388
00:20:02,599 --> 00:20:04,865
A GIRL DEEPLY IN LOVE.

389
00:20:04,865 --> 00:20:07,332
IF YOU REALLY LOVE MYTHO,

390
00:20:07,332 --> 00:20:09,465
THEN YOU MUST WANT
TO CHAT WITH HIM AND SING

391
00:20:09,465 --> 00:20:12,099
AND DANCE WITH HIM, RIGHT?

392
00:20:12,099 --> 00:20:14,299
YOU SAY YOU DON'T MIND
LOSING YOUR HEART,

393
00:20:14,299 --> 00:20:16,765
BUT THAT'S NOT THE REAL YOU!

394
00:20:18,799 --> 00:20:21,599
-UH...

395
00:20:21,599 --> 00:20:23,665
-OH.

396
00:20:31,699 --> 00:20:33,465
-TUTU.

397
00:20:33,465 --> 00:20:34,865
-MYTHO.

398
00:20:34,865 --> 00:20:37,332
-IS THIS ALL A BAD DREAM?

399
00:20:39,865 --> 00:20:41,832
-MYTHO...
-HE'S...

400
00:20:41,832 --> 00:20:45,232
-WHAT?
-ANOTHER ME INSIDE ME IS...

401
00:20:45,232 --> 00:20:48,732
TUTU,
WHAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN TO ME?

402
00:20:48,732 --> 00:20:50,732
-[ GASPS ]

403
00:20:50,732 --> 00:20:54,432
-I...
-MYTHO...

404
00:20:58,099 --> 00:21:00,965
-[ SNORING ]

405
00:21:00,965 --> 00:21:03,332
HMM?

406
00:21:03,332 --> 00:21:05,765
[ DOOR OPENS ]

407
00:21:05,765 --> 00:21:07,599
-GOOD MORNING, PRINCESSES.

408
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:08,799
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

409
00:21:08,799 --> 00:21:10,565
-HEY, WHAT HAPPENED?

410
00:21:10,565 --> 00:21:12,099
-OH, YOU DON'T REMEMBER?

411
00:21:12,099 --> 00:21:16,099
DUCK DRAGGED YOU HOME LATE LAST
NIGHT AND PUT YOU INTO BED.

412
00:21:16,099 --> 00:21:17,599
-HUH?

413
00:21:17,599 --> 00:21:21,765
-THE TWO OF YOU MUST'VE HAD A
MAGNIFICENT, SPECTACULAR BATTLE!

414
00:21:21,765 --> 00:21:23,699
OH, HOW I WISH I'D SEEN IT,

415
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:26,032
BOTH OF YOU ABANDONING
FRIENDSHIP TO FIGHT,

416
00:21:26,032 --> 00:21:27,599
TWO GIRLS IN LOVE WITH MYTHO!

417
00:21:27,599 --> 00:21:29,799
-ME IN LOVE WITH MYTHO?!

418
00:21:29,799 --> 00:21:33,265
OH, YEAH, COME TO THINK OF IT,
I GUESS I WAS, HUH?

419
00:21:33,265 --> 00:21:35,332
-PIKE, THANK GOODNESS.

420
00:21:35,332 --> 00:21:37,032
-SO, HOW'D YOU TWO FIGHT?

421
00:21:37,032 --> 00:21:38,432
-WE DIDN'T!
-WHAT?!

422
00:21:38,432 --> 00:21:40,932
YOU GOT TO BE KIDDING ME!
-BUT, MAN, TO BE HONEST...

423
00:21:40,932 --> 00:21:42,299
I DON'T EVEN KNOW MYSELF

424
00:21:42,299 --> 00:21:44,565
WHY I WAS SO CRAZY ABOUT MYTHO
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

425
00:21:44,565 --> 00:21:46,099
OH!

426
00:21:46,099 --> 00:21:48,399
THAT MUST BE WHAT YOU
CALL THE RASHNESS OF YOUTH!

427
00:21:48,399 --> 00:21:50,732
I'M STICKING TO FAKIR LOVE
FROM NOW ON!

428
00:21:50,732 --> 00:21:53,665
-PRINCESS TUTU IS THE ONLY ONE

429
00:21:53,665 --> 00:21:56,165
WHO CAN GET BACK
THE PRINCE'S HEART,

430
00:21:56,165 --> 00:21:59,499
BUT WHO CAN TURN THE HEART
SOAKED IN RAVEN'S BLOOD

431
00:21:59,499 --> 00:22:00,965
BACK TO NORMAL?

432
00:22:00,965 --> 00:22:04,499
WILL PRINCESS TUTU BE ABLE
TO DO THAT?

433
00:22:04,499 --> 00:22:06,532
[ SLOW MUSIC PLAYS ]

434
00:22:17,599 --> 00:22:19,632
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

435
00:22:49,599 --> 00:22:51,632
[ SINGING IN JAPANESE
CONTINUES ]

436
00:23:34,432 --> 00:23:37,499
-IS SOMETHING HAPPENING BEHIND
THE SCENES WHERE I CAN'T SEE IT?

437
00:23:37,499 --> 00:23:39,232
I DON'T WANT TO FIGHT ANYMORE.

438
00:23:39,232 --> 00:23:40,799
-IT WOULD BE WONDERFUL

439
00:23:40,799 --> 00:23:42,865
IF THE WORLD WERE
FULL OF FLOWERS, WOULDN'T IT?

440
00:23:42,865 --> 00:23:45,465
-YOUR BEAUTIFUL HEART
MAKES BEAUTIFUL FLOWERS BLOOM.

441
00:23:45,465 --> 00:23:47,399
-I WAS LOOKING FOR A TAIL,
AND I FOUND HER BUTT, ZURA!

442
00:23:47,399 --> 00:23:49,265
-WELL, HER NAME IS UZURA.

443
00:23:49,265 --> 00:23:51,599
KARON MADE HER FROM THE WOOD
FROM EDEL THAT DIDN'T BURN UP.

444
00:23:51,599 --> 00:23:53,632
-KRAEHE,
WHAT HAVE YOU DONE TO MYTHO?

445
00:23:53,632 --> 00:23:56,565
-THE ONE WHO MADE THE PRINCE
LIKE THIS IS YOU, TUTU.

446
00:23:56,565 --> 00:23:58,065
-WHY?! WHY WON'T YOU LOVE ME?!

447
00:23:58,065 --> 00:24:02,399
-ALL YOU CHILDREN WHO LOVE
STORIES, COME GATHER 'ROUND.

448
00:24:02,399 --> 00:24:04,199
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

